# WHAT IT IS
#   git-rewrite-commits is "an AI-powered git commit message
#   rewriter using Ollama, OpenAI GPT, or Claude Code".  Run it
#   against a branch and it analyzes every commit's diff,
#   detects well-formed conventional-commit messages (skipping
#   them by default), then asks the configured LLM to write a
#   cleaner message for every commit that falls below the
#   configured quality score.  Safety-first defaults:  a backup
#   branch is created automatically before rewriting history;
#   `--dry-run` previews changes without touching git;  remote
#   API calls require explicit consent (`--skip-remote-consent`
#   for CI).  Optional `--install-hooks` deploys companion
#   `pre-commit` + `prepare-commit-msg` hooks that generate
#   conformant messages at commit time using the same LLM.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/cli.ts — Commander
#                       v12 `program.option(...)` chain)
#   git-rewrite-commits [OPTIONS]
#
#   Provider / model:
#     --provider <PROVIDER>          AI provider
#                                    (openai | ollama |
#                                     claude-code)
#                                    [default: openai]
#     -k, --api-key <KEY>            OpenAI API key
#                                    [env: OPENAI_API_KEY]
#     -m, --model <MODEL>            AI model
#                                    [default: gpt-3.5-turbo for
#                                              OpenAI;
#                                              llama3.2 for
#                                              Ollama; haiku
#                                              for Claude Code]
#     --ollama-url <URL>             Ollama server URL
#                                    [default: http://localhost:
#                                              11434]
#
#   Git scope:
#     -b, --branch <BRANCH>          Branch to rewrite
#                                    [default: current branch]
#     --max-commits <N>              Process only the last N
#                                    commits
#     --skip-backup                  Skip the safety-backup
#                                    branch (not recommended)
#     --staged                       Generate a message for
#                                    staged changes (for git
#                                    hooks)
#
#   Filtering:
#     --no-skip-well-formed          Process all commits,
#                                    even well-formed ones
#     --min-quality-score <SCORE>    Minimum quality score
#                                    1.0-10.0 to count as
#                                    well-formed
#
#   Message formatting:
#     -t, --template <FORMAT>        Custom commit message
#                                    template (e.g.
#                                    "(feat): message" or
#                                    "[JIRA-XXX] type: message")
#     -l, --language <LANG>          Language for messages
#                                    [default: en]
#     -p, --prompt <TEXT>            Custom prompt (overrides
#                                    default instructions)
#
#   Diagnostics / safety:
#     -d, --dry-run                  Show what would change
#                                    without modifying the repo
#     -v, --verbose                  Detailed output (diffs +
#                                    file changes)
#     -q, --quiet                    Suppress informational
#                                    output (useful for git
#                                    hooks)
#     --skip-remote-consent          Skip consent prompt for
#                                    remote API calls (CI only)
#
#   Hook installer:
#     --install-hooks                Install pre-commit and
#                                    prepare-commit-msg hooks
#                                    (opt-in;  the hooks
#                                    themselves require
#                                    explicit `git config
#                                    hooks.preCommitPreview
#                                    true` /
#                                    `hooks.prepareCommitMsg
#                                    true` to activate)
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
